						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup in front of the agasi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is an incomplete record. It contains only the date portion <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Āngīrasa, Mārgaśira, Su. 1 without the Śaka year. It is in 17th century characters. The cyclic year Angīrasa occurred twice during this century: (1) Śaka 1554 = 1632 A.D., and (2) Śaka 1614 = 1692 A.D.</p>						

						<p>At the end the word ‘Atanū’ is mentioned. Probably it refers to Atanūru, the place of the origin of this record.</p>						

						</summary>
